<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIFTH SUSPECT IN PASADENA SLAYINGS OF 3 SURRENDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The fifth suspect sought in the Halloween slayings of three Pasadena 
teen-agers will be arraigned today in Pasadena Municipal Court after 
surrendering at police headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 Herbert McClain, 25, who fled to the Midwest for a time, walked into Pasadena 
police headquarters and told police he was "tired of looking over his 
shoulder," Lt. Denis Petersen said. 
</P>
<P>
 He is the last suspect sought in the ambush killings of Edgar Evans, 13, and 
Stephen Coats and Reggie Crawford, both 14, as they walked home from a 
Halloween party. 
</P>
<P>
 Police say the suspects, all reputed Pasadena gang members, were angry at the 
shooting of one of their gang colleagues and may have mistakenly shot the three 
teen-agers, who had no gang ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA011994-0017 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 005166 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
January 19, 1994, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
