 "We have nowhere to go. We have no money, no clothes but the ones we have on, 
and no papers. I don't know where we will go." 
</P>
<P>
 Pedro Barajas, who fled with his eight children from the devastated Fillmore 
Hotel 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think we're going to rebuild. We'll probably sell the bricks." 
</P>
