<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: EARTHQUAKE CAUSES HOLD ON TROUT PLANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Because of road closures and other problems associated with Monday morning's 
earthquake, Department of Fish and Game trout plants scheduled this week for 
Los Angeles County reservoirs -- which come from a hatchery in Fillmore -- have 
been put on hold indefinitely. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokeswoman at the Long Beach office said it has not been determined when 
the planting would resume. Trout stocked in Orange, San Bernardino and San 
Diego county waters come from a hatchery in Mojave, and stocking programs were 
not affected by the earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Fishing reports were not available at some locations because of lack of 
telephone service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
