<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: DANA HILLS' CRUICKSHANK DECIDES ON WASHINGTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Cruickshank, a defensive lineman from Dana Hills, made an oral 
commitment to Washington, former Dana Hills Coach Jack Murry said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cruickshank, a 6-foot-6, 230-pound Times second-team all-county selection and 
first-team All-Southern Section Division I pick, chose Washington over USC. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills' quarterback Scott Covington (Miami) and linebacker Matt Schuetz 
(Oregon), made commitments Monday.  
</P>
<P>
 Linebacker Vic Harper, wide receiver Mike Whitaker and defensive lineman Jesus 
Morales made oral commitments to the Merchant Marine Academy, a Division III 
program in Kings Point, N.Y., Murry said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Bertoni, Fountain Valley quarterback, has made an oral commitment to 
Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
 Bertoni, a 6-1 1/2, 180-pound senior who passed for more than 2,000 yards and 
21 touchdowns, chose Nevada over Colorado State and New Mexico State. 
</P>
<P>
 "They may not have the big-time schedules the Pac-10 schools have, but they 
have great facilities . . . and you can breathe up there," Bertoni said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Phelps, Irvine quarterback, has decided to commit to Oregon after 
visiting Eugene recently, Irvine Athletic Director Rick Curtis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Phelps, 6 feet 5, 210 pounds, guided the Vaqueros to the Southern Section 
Division IV championship, their third title in three seasons.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Gonzalez, a tight end from Huntington Beach, was the only Orange County 
player selected to the Schutt Sports Group All-American High School football 
team. 
</P>
<P>
 Scholastic Coach publication coordinated a group of coaches, writers and 
recruiters to choose the 100-player team. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodney Sermons of La Puente Bishop Amat, George Perry of San Bernardino and 
Matt Redman of Palos Verdes Peninsula were the only other Southern Section 
players named. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez, who has orally committed to California and will play football and 
basketball, helped Huntington Beach reach the Division II finals last season. 
MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
