<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFICA TIES COUNTY RECORD FOR SCORING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tonie Mascarenas and Colleen Morris each scored four goals as Pacifica tied 
the Orange County single-game girls' record for goals in a 17-0 victory over 
Santiago in a Garden Grove League soccer game Tuesday at Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
 Valerie Downen had five assists for Pacifica (7-4, 5-2 in league) and Sara 
Brown and Joy Guenther each scored two goals. Pacifica led, 10-0, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mariners tied the mark of 17 goals set by La Quinta in the 1984-85 season. 
Temple City holds the Southern Section record with 19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
