<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER ROUNDUP; VALENCIA, BREA-OLINDA KEEP SCORELESS STREAKS GOING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Entering Tuesday's game, the Valencia and Brea-Olinda girls' soccer teams 
hadn't been scored on in Orange League play and both left with their streaks 
intact, playing to a 0-0 tie at Brea-Olinda High. 
</P>
<P>
 The tie kept the Wildcats (5-6-3, 3-0-1) a half-game in front of Valencia 
(5-6-4, 2-0-2) as they pursue a second consecutive league championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia entered the game with impressive credentials as well, finishing 
either first or second in the league standings since 1985 and qualifying for 
the playoffs each season since 1981. 
</P>
<P>
 Defense was a priority as the teams were limited to nine shots each. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia fullbacks Casey West and Alicia Franklin teamed to break up several 
Wildcat scoring chances while Brea-Olinda's Tracy Tremayne and Stacey Seiler 
used their quickness to beat the Tiger forwards to the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda's best chance to score came six minutes into the second half when 
Katie O'Brien passed the ball ahead to Desiree Hitchcock, who had slipped past 
a Tiger defender. However, Hitchcock's left-footer was aimed directly at 
Valencia goalkeeper Woodi Taylor, who made the save. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia had a scoring opportunity with about five minutes remaining when Amy 
Ensman was awarded a free kick just outside the penalty box. 
</P>
<P>
 Ensman's shot hit a wall of Brea defenders and bounced straight back giving 
her a second attempt. This time her shot got through the defense, but sailed 
inches above the crossbar. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
