<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPER BOWL LINEBACKER CAFFEY DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lee Roy Caffey, a linebacker for three Super Bowl champions, died Tuesday at 
52 of colon cancer. 
</P>
<P>
 Caffey spent 10 years with the Green Bay Packers, Dallas Cowboys and San Diego 
Chargers, playing on the Packer teams that won the first two Super Bowls and 
with the 1972 Super Bowl Champion Cowboys. 
</P>
<P>
 He graduated from Texas A&M in 1963 and was a resident of College Station. 
</P>
</TEXT>
