<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nikki Clark 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Guard 
</P>
<P>
 Clark took the long way to Fullerton.After a standout career at Brea-Olinda 
High, Clark played at Golden West last season. But when things didn't work out 
as expected she left the Rustlers at midseason. Clark has been Fullerton's most 
steady player this season, averaging a team-best 10 points. Clark had 17 points 
in the Hornets' 64-54 loss to Orange Coast last Wednesday, then scored 17 more 
as Fullerton upset host Riverside, 49-46, Friday. She also leads Fullerton with 
66 assists and 62 steals. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Julie Murdent scored 24 points on 11 of 17 shooting as Golden West beat 
Orange Coast, 79-71, in overtime Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
