<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; AUTHOR TO TALK ON GETTING KIDS TO READ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Trelease, author of the "Read-Aloud Handbook," will offer parents tips on 
getting children to choose reading over watching television during a seminar at 
Ada E. Clegg Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
 The lecture, geared for parents, teachers and librarians, will be held Jan. 25 
at 7 p.m, said event coordinator Mary Brummett. 
</P>
<P>
 He will discuss how reading with children can make a difference in a child's 
attitudes toward books and learning, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are available at Clegg, at 6311 Larchwood Drive, for $2 before the 
lecture and $3 at the door. For tickets or more information, call (714) 
894-7218. 
</P>
