<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; TRUSTEES PROMOTE, HIRE PRINCIPALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback Valley Unified School District trustees have approved the promotion 
of one high school principal and the hiring of another. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo High School Principal Robert Metz will be the district's 
director of secondary education.Metz will be responsible for instruction at the 
district's four high schools, four intermediate schools and the continuation 
school. 
</P>
<P>
 Metz has been a principal for 17 years, including 12 at Mission Viejo High. He 
will continue as principal there until a replacement is hired. 
</P>
<P>
 The trustees last week also approved the appointment of George Diedrich as 
principal of Trabuco Hills High School. Currently principal of South High 
School in Denver, Diedrich was selected from a field of 40 candidates from 
around the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 He has a master's degree in educational administration from the University of 
Colorado and has been an educator in that state since 1967, the last 13 as a 
principal. 
</P>
<P>
 Diedrich will take the Trabuco Hills High post on April 11. 
</P>
