<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALTRANS NAMES NEW CHIEF FOR LOCAL DISTRICT; TRANSPORTATION: BRENT FELKER, WHO 
IS OVERSEEING THE SANTA ANA FREEWAY WIDENING, WILL ASSUME THE POST OF DIRECTOR 
MONDAY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 33-year-old project manager overseeing the widening of the Santa Ana Freeway 
has been named to head Caltrans' Orange County District, officials confirmed 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Brent Felker, now serving as deputy district director for construction in the 
county, will assume the post Monday, California Department of Transportation 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "As the new district director I will continue the improvements needed to 
develop a multi-modal system here in Orange County," Felker said, including 
high-occupancy freeway lanes, rail lines and express bus systems. 
</P>
<P>
 Felker has spent much of his time in recent years overseeing the widening of 
the freeway through Santa Ana and Irvine, plans for new on- and off-ramps for 
Disneyland in Anaheim and the redesigning of the El Toro "Y." 
</P>
<P>
 "Transportation officials in Orange County and throughout the state are going 
to continue to focus on making improvements," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Felker said he had just completed a preliminary survey of possible earthquake 
damage to the county's freeway construction, bridges, overpasses and 
underpasses. He said he had identified no damage in the county on the state 
highway system. 
</P>
<P>
 In an earlier interview, Felker said that the freeway construction now going 
on in the county "is essentially unique to the state. . . . It's like 
conducting open-heart surgery while keeping the patient walking or running. . . 
. Our drive is to keep people moving." 
</P>
<P>
 He said that construction on the Santa Ana Freeway has not scared drivers off 
the route, as sometimes happens during major traffic accidents or other 
tie-ups. During the construction, he said, traffic on the freeway has remained 
constant -- about 250,000 to 300,000 vehicles daily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
