<P>
WORLD WATCH: NESTLE PLANS NEW DAIRY PRODUCTION IN CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Swiss company said it plans to invest $45 million in two dairy product 
ventures in Qingdao in the province of Shandong in eastern China.The joint 
ventures -- Nestle will hold a 75% stake in each -- are with Qingdao Milk 
Course Co. One operation will produce products such as sweetened condensed milk 
and milk powder. The other will be used for ice cream and yogurt production. 
Nestle has three factories operating in China, and "business is growing at a 
very satisfactory rate," the company said. 
</P>
