<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. ARTISTS AND ART ORGANIZATIONS TO GET GRANTS FROM GETTY TRUST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles artists John Outterbridge, Caren Carson, John Valadez, Liz Young 
and Tom Knechtel have been selected to each receive $15,000 unrestricted 
fellowships from the J. Paul Getty Trust Fund for the Visual Arts. 
</P>
<P>
 Several local arts organizations will also receive Getty grants, including 
East Los Angeles' Self-Help Graphics and Art ($21,500), the Santa Monica Museum 
of Art ($18,000), Plaza de la Raza ($14,250), Santa Monica's 18th Street Arts 
Complex ($10,000) and the Gay and Lesbian Media Coalition ($7,500). 
</P>
<P>
 Other recipients include Long Beach's Homeland Neighborhood Cultural Center 
($9,000), LAX: The Los Angeles Exhibition ($8,450), Venice's Social and Public 
Art Resource Center ($7,000), Angels Gate Cultural Center ($7,000) and L.A. 
Artcore ($2,300). 
</P>
<P>
 The annual Getty grants are administered by the California Community 
Foundation. Information: (213) 413-4042. 
</P>
