<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTHQUAKE / THE LONG ROAD BACK; FINDING YOUR ROUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Navigating the Southland's quake-mangled freeway system will take planning and 
perseverance, probably for many months ahead. Here are the major road closures 
and some alternate routes around them: Roads 
</P>
<P>
 The following roads are closed: 
</P>
<P>
 1. Pacific Coast Highway, from Santa Monica Freeway at McClure Tunnel to 
Temescal Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Northbound: Take 405 Freeway, west on Sunset Boulevard, 
left on Temescal Canyon to Pacific Coast Highway. Southbound: Left on Temescal 
Canyon, east on Sunset Boulevard to the 405 Freeway south. 
</P>
<P>
 2. Golden State Freeway (I-5) northbound, closed at Antelope Valley Freeway 
because of bridge damage, but truck lane to Antelope Valley Freeway is open. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Take northbound Antelope Valley Freeway to San Fernando 
Road (Route 126), left on Lyons Avenue to I-5. 
</P>
<P>
 3. The southbound Golden State (I-5) Freeway is closed between Lyons Avenue 
and the Foothill Freeway (210), and the northbound Golden State Freeway is 
closed from the Antelope Valley Freeway to Lyons Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Lyons Avenue, east to San Fernando Road (Route 
126), south on Sierra Highway to San Fernando Road, south on Sepulveda 
Boulevard to Roxford Street to I-5. 
</P>
<P>
 4. The eastbound Santa Monica Freeway is closed from Centinela Avenue to 
Washington Boulevard because of bridge collapse. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit Pico Boulevard or Centinela Avenue. Use eastbound Pico 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 5. The westbound Santa Monica Freeway is closed from Washington Boulevard to 
the San Diego Freeway (405) interchange because of a bridge collapse. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Washington Boulevard to Apple Street, right on 
Fairfax Avenue, left at Venice Boulevard, right at Cadillac Avenue, left at La 
Cienega Boulevard to westbound Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 6. The westbound Santa Monica Freeway connector to the southbound San Diego 
Freeway is closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Westbound exit at Overland Boulevard, take National 
Boulevard left onto southbound 405 Freeway on-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
 7. Eastbound Simi Valley Freeway (118) is closed from Tampa Avenue to the San 
Diego Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit onto southbound De Soto Avenue or Tampa Avenue to 
Devonshire Street, left on Devonshire Street to 405, 5 or 210 freeways. 
</P>
<P>
 8. Westbound Simi Valley Freeway is closed from the Foothill Freeway to the 
San Diego Freeway. All connectors from the Golden State and Foothill freeways 
are also closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: From northbound 405 Freeway, exit at Roscoe Boulevard or 
Devonshire Street, left to Tampa Avenue or De Soto Avenue, right to westbound 
Simi Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 9. All connectors from the westbound Foothill Freeway to the westbound Simi 
Valley Freeway are closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Foothill Freeway through lanes are open. 
</P>
<P>
 10. All connectors from the westbound Foothill Freeway to the Golden State 
Freeway are closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit Foothill Freeway on Roxford Boulevard, proceed west to 
I-5. 
</P>
<P>
 11. The northbound San Diego Freeway is closed at Devonshire Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Nordhoff Street, east on Nordhoff Street to I-5 
northbound. 
</P>
<P>
 12. The northbound San Diego Freeway connector to the westbound Simi Valley 
Freeway is closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Nordhoff Street, west to Tampa Avenue, then north 
to westbound Simi Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 13. The southbound San Diego Freeway is closed at Rinaldi Street. 
</P>
<P>
 For freeway information, call (800) 427-7623 Rail 
</P>
<P>
 Amtrak service between Los Angeles and San Luis Obispo will resume at 8 a.m. 
today. Call 800 USA-RAIL for information. Mass Transit 
</P>
<P>
 MTA bus lines, including the Blue Line trains and Red Line subway, are in full 
service. There will be intermittent detours as workers clear earthquake damage 
on the following bus lines: 
</P>
<P>
 Line 90: Los Angeles, Sunland and Sylmar (via Pennsylvania Avenue) 
</P>
<P>
 Line 94: Los Angeles, San Fernando, Sylmar (via San Fernando Road) 
</P>
<P>
 Line 236: From Ventura Boulevard to Rinaldi Street and north/south on Woodley 
Avenue and Balboa Boulevard 
</P>
<P>
 Line 243: From Woodland Hills along Ventura Boulevard to Winnetka Avenue 
</P>
<P>
 There are also plans to operate a new line between Santa Monica and Downtown 
Los Angeles. For information about bus and train schedules, call (213) 
244-6347, (818) 781-5860 or (818) 246-2593. 
</P>
<P>
 Metrolink: Five cars will be added to trains on the Santa Clarita line. 
</P>
<P>
 The following train lines will resume service at 8 a.m. today: 100, 102, 103, 
104, 105, 106, 107, 108, 109, 110 and 111. For more information, call (800) 
371-LINK. Tough Time for Truckers 
</P>
<P>
 Truckers were left stranded in the San Joaquin Valley; such tie-ups may have 
economic reverberations. Map shows suggested alternative routes for the state's 
long-distance truckers. 
</P>
