<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTHQUAKE / THE LONG ROAD BACK; CORONER'S OFFICE RELEASES PARTIAL LIST OF 
QUAKE DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County coroner's office Tuesday night identified 30 of the 40 
people who died as a result of the earthquake, including 12 of the 16 who died 
when the first floor of a Northridge apartment building collapsed. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who died in the collapse were: 
</P>
<P>
 Angeline (Ann) Cerone, 80; Sharon Englar, 58; Phil Englar, 62; Darla Raye 
Enos, 43; Cecilia Pressman, 72; David Pressman, 72; Bea Reskin, 71; Jaime 
Reyes, 19; Karol Runnings, 48; Manuel D. Sandoval, 24; Adam Slotnik, 27, and 
Myrna Velasquez, 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Others who died in the quake were: 
</P>
<P>
 Jerry Borman, 67, Santa Clarita; Pearl Carr, 70, Granada Hills; Norman Cole, 
79, Granada Hills; Burton Krell, 59, of Northridge; Los Angeles Police Officer 
Clarence W. Dean, 46; Ted Peter Fichtner, 28; Hannah Kamiya, 75, Los Angeles; 
Gennady Khytman, 45, West Hollywood; Kevin C. Maher, 25, Sherman Oaks; Antionia 
Munoz, 66; Concha Quintanar, 83, San Fernando; Madeline Riggins, 92, Panorama 
City; Amy Vigil-Tyre, 5; Olga Robles Uribe, 26; Margarita Vasquez, 90; Lionel 
Ventura, 20, Sun Valley; Marc Yobf, 32, Sherman Oaks, and Karen Osterholt, 30, 
Sherman Oaks. 
</P>
