<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Birtcher Medical Systems Inc.: The Irvine surgical instrument maker Tuesday 
said it expects a second-quarter loss of more than six cents a share because of 
severe price competition and flat revenue.The company expects to report 
official results later this week. For the second quarter a year ago, the 
company lost $900,000, or 10 cents a share, on $11 million in revenue. For the 
first quarter this year, Birtcher's loss totaled $507,000, or 6 cents a share, 
on revenue of $10.1 million. 
</P>
