</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TH&M Advertising Inc. has moved from the airport area to smaller offices in 
Old Town Irvine.The agency is in a former pinto bean warehouse, said Jim 
Hughes, president and creative director. 
</P>
<P>
 He said the move reflects a shrinking staff. The agency is down to a dozen 
people, from 35 at one point. 
</P>
<P>
 Hughes said he started consciously whittling the staff last summer so he could 
offer clients a pay-as-you-go service instead of charging a retainer fee. 
</P>
<P>
 "I put senior staff people in charge of key departments" and they hire 
contract workers as needed, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
