<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV RATINGS; ABC EKES OUT VICTORY; NBC SCORES BIG ON THURSDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the tight ratings battle this season, ABC pulled out another close victory, 
finishing one-tenth of a ratings point behind leader CBS last week and pulling 
within two-tenths of a ratings point behind CBS for the entire season, 
according to A.C. Nielsen Co. figures released Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 ABC finished the week with a 13.4 rating and five of the top 10 shows, led by 
the season's top-rated program, "Home Impovement," at No. 2. CBS averaged a 
13.3 rating for the week, followed by NBC's 11.5 and Fox's 7.3. (Each ratings 
point represents 942,000 TV households.) 
</P>
<P>
 NBC scored huge on Thursday night with two episodes of the surging sitcom "Mad 
About You," which won the 8-9 p.m. time period. More impressively, the two 
following episodes of "Seinfeld" were repeats from 1991, but they finished as 
the No. 4 and No. 5 programs of the week and ranked as the second and third 
highest-rated "Seinfeld" telecasts ever. 
</P>
<P>
 Fox premiered two new shows last week. "Monty," starring Henry Winkler as a 
conservative radio talk-show host, finished No. 79 out of 94 prime-time 
programs, but posted Fox's highest Tuesday-night performance to date with an 
8.6 rating. "The George Carlin Show" did even better, finishing No. 43 last 
Sunday night while holding onto 94% of the lead-in audience provided by 
"Married. . .With Children." Southland Ratings 
</P>
<P>
 Here are A. C. Nielsen's Top 10 prime-time programs in the Los Angeles area 
during the same week. Each rating point equals 50,064 households. 
